      </div>
      <h1 class='title'>Tourism Revenues (Royal Family)</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 16 September 2004 vol 424 c1702WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_1702ws' title='Col. 1702WS &mdash; HC Deb 16 September 2004 vol 424 c1702WS' name='column_1702ws' href='#column_1702ws' rel='bookmark'>1702WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_293'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-andrew-rosindell' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_293' title='Link to this speech by Mr Andrew Rosindell' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-andrew-rosindell" title="Mr Andrew Rosindell">Mr. Rosindell</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport what estimate she has made of the amount of revenue generated by tourism related to the royal family in summer 2004.[189204]</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_294'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-richard-caborn' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0424P2_20040916_CWS2_294' title='Link to this speech by Mr Richard Caborn' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-richard-caborn" title="Mr Richard Caborn">Mr. Caborn</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">No estimate is made of the amount of revenue generated by the royal family in relation to tourism. The royal family and its heritage is a major factor in attracting visitors to Britain. They are a key part of Britain's successful tourism industry which is worth &#x00A3;76 billion to the economy. The royal family is very supportive of the tourism industry and their commitment will continue to bring great economic benefits to Britain.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
